SENECA, the famous philosopher, was born at Corduba, in Spain, a few years before the Christian era. His parents belonged to the equestrian order and were rich. His father was a rhetorician, and remains of several of his oratorical works have come down to us. Seneca was br ought to Rome when a child, and though of feeble constitution was a de- voted student.
